    <h2>Using local data storage</h2>

</head>


    <h3>Mikel's NoteBook</h3>
    <p>You can use the local storage on your device to save a note for yourself. Just type a note, save it, and next time you open this site it will have the note for you.</p>
    <textarea name='notepad' id='notepad' cols="40" rows="5">Type a note to yourself here.</textarea><br>
    <button type="button" onclick="notebook()">Save your note</button>
    <p>Next time you load this page, this note will display:</p> <p id="results"></p>
    <script>
        function notebook() {
            if (typeof (Storage) !== "undefined") {

             localStorage.setItem("savedNote", String(document.getElementById('notepad').value));
             document.getElementById("results").innerHTML = localStorage.getItem("savedNote");
            } else {
                document.getElementById("notepad").innerHTML = "Sorry, no local storage."
            }
        }
    </script>
    
    
    <p>Your most recent note:</p>
    <div id="result" style="border:solid; length:100px; width:300px"></div>
    

<script>
// Check browser support
if (typeof(Storage) !== "undefined") {
    // Store
    localStorage.setItem("myNote", localStorage.getItem("savedNote"));
    // Retrieve
    document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = localStorage.getItem("myNote");
} else {
    document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = "Sorry, your browser does not support Web Storage...";
}
</script>
   
    
    
    


